s into Abar]]\n| date8     = December 8, 2019\n| rs8       = 0.3\n| viewers8  = 0.822<ref name=\"1.08\"/>\n| dvr8      =\n| dvrv8     =\n| total8    =\n| totalv8   =\n\n| title9    = [[See How They Fly]]\n| date9     = December 15, 2019\n| rs9       = 0.3\n| viewers9  = 0.935<ref name=\"1.09\"/>\n| dvr9      =\n| dvrv9     =\n| total9    = \n| totalv9   =\n}}\n\n===Audience viewership===\nAccording to HBO, the first episode of ''Watchmen'' had more than 1.5 million viewers on its first night across television and streaming services, the strongest debut performance for the network. The first broadcast of the episode, at 9 p.m. EDT, had 800,000 viewers, making it the most viewed debut episode for any premium-cable show in 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/watchmen-ratings-regina-king-damon-lindelof-hbo-digital-1202765310/ |title=''Watchmen'' Premiere Draws 1.5 Million Viewers, Delivering Strongest Digital Debut For HBO Since 'Westworld' |first=Dino-Ray |last=Ramos |date=October 21, 2019 |accessdate=October 21, 2019 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref> The second episode dropped to about 1.3 million viewers across the first night, with 765,000 watching the first broadcast, though this was considered a strong performance as the show aired alongside Game 5 of the [[2019 World Series]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/tv-ratings-watchmen-episode-2-viewership-1203387421/ |title=TV Ratings: ''Watchmen'' Episode 2 Dips, Still Draws 1.3 Million Viewers |first=Will |last=Thorne |date=October 29, 2019 |accessdate=October 29, 2019 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n\nAs of episode 6, HBO reported 7 million viewers to date, making it HBO's most viewed new series since ''[[Big Little Lies (TV series)|Big Little Lies]]''. In addition it has contributed  to the largest digital viewership for a freshman series since ''[[Westworld (TV series)|Westworld]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://whatculture.com/tv/why-nobody-is-watching-the-watchmen |title=Why Nobody Is Watching The Watchmen |last=Paterson |first=Ewan |date=November 27, 2019 |website=WhatCulture.com |access-date=November 29, 2019}}</ref> HBO estimates that the Sunday night premiere viewership represents only about 10% of the total viewership for an episode, to the effect of word-of-mouth that has brought new viewers to the show, with the first episode having a total of 9.6 million viewers as of December 4, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/hbo-watchmen-ratings-1203425067/ |title=TV Ratings: HBO's ''Watchmen'' Is a Word of Mouth Hit |first=Kate |last=Aurthur |date=December 4, 2019 |accessdate=December 4, 2019 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"23\" | 2019\n| [[American Film Institute Awards 2019|American Film Institute Awards]]\n| scope=\"row\" | Television Programs of the Year\n| scope=\"row\" | ''Watchmen''\n| {{Won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/film/awards/scorsese-irishman-joker-1917-afi-1203424814/ |title=AFI Awards: Top Films and TV Shows Include 'Joker,' 'Farewell,' 'Succession,' ''Watchmen'' |first=Jazz |last=Tangcay |date=December 4, 2019 |accessdate=December 4, 2019 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Clio Awards]]\n| Television/Streaming: Teaser\n| \"Tick Tock\"\n| {{Won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/clio-entertainment-awards-2019-winners-list-1256709/item/games-innovation-clio-entertainment-awards-winners-2019-1256713 |title=Clio Entertainment Awards 2019: 'Joker,' 'Us,' 'Game of Thrones' Among Top Winners |last=Howard |first=Annie |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=November 21, 2019