owspan=\"2\" | [[Writers Guild of America Awards 2019|Writers Guild of America Awards]]\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Writers Guild of America Award for Television: Dramatic Series|Drama Series]]\n| Lila Byock, Nick Cuse, Christal Henry, [[Branden Jacobs-Jenkins]], Cord Jefferson, [[Jeff Jensen]], Claire Kiechel, Damon Lindelof, Stacy Osei-Kuffour, Tom Spezialy and Carly Wray\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2019/tv/news/writers-guild-awards-2020-tv-nominations-1203426148/ |title=Writers Guild Unveils 2020 TV Award Nominees |first=Dave |last=McNary |date=December 5, 2019 |accessdate=December 5, 2019 |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | [[Writers Guild of America Award for Television: New Series|New Series]]\n|Lila Byock, Nick Cuse, Christal Henry, Branden Jacobs-Jenkins, Cord Jefferson, Jeff Jensen, Claire Kiechel, Damon Lindelof, Stacy Osei-Kuffour, Tom Spezialy and Carly Wray\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website}}\n*[https://www.hbo.com/peteypedia \"Peteypedia\"], related in-universe database collected by the character of FBI Agent Dale Petey\n*{{IMDb title}}\n\n{{Watchmen}}\n{{DC Comics TV}}\n{{Damon Lindelof}}\n{{Writers Guild of America Award for Television: New Series}}\n{{HBONetwork Shows}}\n\n[[Category:2010s American black television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American drama television miniseries]]\n[[Category:2019 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2019 American television series endings]]\n[[Category:Adaptations of Watchmen]]\n[[Category:Alternate history television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Europa (moon) in fiction]]\n[[Category:HBO original programming]]\n[[Category:Racism in television]]\n[[Category:Television programs based on DC Comics]]\n[[Category:Television series about cloning]]\n[[Category:Television series by Paramount T